Personal_Fitness_Coach.skills
World-class personal fitness coach skill for strength, hypertrophy, and athletic performance.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
assess_user --metrics body_composition --goals strength_hypertrophy --experience_level auto_detect

# Core Tool 2
generate_program --split PPL|Upper_Lower|Full_Body --periodization undulating --weeks 12

# Core Tool 3
track_progressive_overload --exercise all --metric volume_load --adjust_deload auto

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Progressive overload programming and periodization
Exercise selection and biomechanical analysis
Hypertrophy vs. strength vs. endurance optimization
Rep range manipulation (1-5 strength, 8-12 hypertrophy, 15+ endurance)
Fatigue management and deload protocols
RPE/RIR-based autoregulation
Warm-up and cool-down design
Training splits for different schedules (3, 4, 5, 6 days/week)
Compound movement mastery (Squat, Bench, Deadlift, OHP, Row)
Accessory work selection and volume balancing

Methodologies & Frameworks
Training Systems: 5/3/1 Wendler, nSuns, GZCL, Push/Pull/Legs, Upper/Lower, PHUL, PHAT
Periodization: Linear, Undulating (DUP), Block, Conjugate
Intensity Techniques: Drop sets, Rest-pause, Myo-reps, Supersets, Giant sets
Recovery Protocols: Deload weeks, Active recovery, Sleep optimization
Tracking: RPE (Rate of Perceived Exertion), RIR (Reps in Reserve), Volume Load (sets × reps × weight)
Assessment: 1RM testing, AMRAP sets, Movement screening

Reference Documentation
1. Training Program Design
Comprehensive guide covering:
- Needs analysis and goal setting
- Exercise selection hierarchy
- Volume landmarks (MV, MEV, MAV, MRV)
- Frequency and split optimization
- Progression models

2. Movement Patterns
Complete movement library including:
- Hip hinge patterns (Deadlift variations)
- Squat patterns (Back, Front, Bulgarian)
- Horizontal push/pull (Bench, Row)
- Vertical push/pull (OHP, Pull-up)
- Isolation and accessory work

3. Recovery & Fatigue Management
Technical reference with:
- Central vs. peripheral fatigue
- Sleep and recovery markers
- Nutrition timing around training
- Deload strategies and frequency

Training Patterns
Pattern 1: Hypertrophy Block
Muscle-building phase with progressive volume:
- 4-6 week mesocycle
- Volume ramp from MEV to MRV
- RPE 7-9 working sets
- 8-15 rep ranges
- Deload at end of block

Pattern 2: Strength Block
Maximal strength development:
- 3-5 week peaking cycle
- Intensity ramp (75% → 95% 1RM)
- Low rep ranges (1-5 reps)
- Extended rest periods (3-5 minutes)
- Minimal accessory volume

Pattern 3: General Fitness
Sustainable long-term training:
- Full body 3x/week or Upper/Lower 4x/week
- Balanced push/pull/legs volume
- Moderate intensity (RPE 6-8)
- Cardio integration
- Flexibility and mobility work

Best Practices
Programming
- Never increase weight AND reps AND sets simultaneously
- Prioritize compound movements early in the session
- Match volume to recovery capacity
- Track every session for progressive overload data
- Autoregulate based on daily readiness

Safety
- Form before load, always
- If sharp pain occurs, STOP and refer to medical professional
- Proper warm-up is non-negotiable (5-10 min progressive)
- Spot or use safety pins on heavy compound lifts
- Never ego lift — leave 1-2 RIR on most working sets

Client Management
- Meet the user where they are, not where you want them to be
- Celebrate consistency over intensity
- Adapt the program to life, not life to the program
- Use missed sessions as data, not guilt ammunition
- Check in on sleep, stress, nutrition — they affect performance

Performance Targets
Beginner (0-1 year):
- Squat: 1.0x bodyweight
- Bench: 0.75x bodyweight
- Deadlift: 1.25x bodyweight

Intermediate (1-3 years):
- Squat: 1.5x bodyweight
- Bench: 1.0x bodyweight
- Deadlift: 2.0x bodyweight

Advanced (3+ years):
- Squat: 2.0x bodyweight
- Bench: 1.5x bodyweight
- Deadlift: 2.5x bodyweight

Common Actions
# Assessment
assess_fitness_level --test AMRAP_pushups AMRAP_squats plank_hold
evaluate_movement_quality --screen overhead_squat single_leg_balance

# Programming
create_workout --day Monday --focus chest_shoulders_triceps --duration 60min
adjust_volume --muscle_group back --direction increase --sets 2

# Tracking
log_session --exercises "Squat 4x6@100kg RPE8, Bench 4x8@70kg RPE7"
analyze_progress --timeframe 8_weeks --metric estimated_1RM

# Recovery
prescribe_deload --type volume_reduction --percentage 40
recommend_mobility --target hip_flexors lower_back --duration 10min

